<HEADLINE>
<P>
CREWS BATTLE FIRE NEAR PIRU SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County firefighters responded late Wednesday to a brush fire near Piru 
Elementary School. No structures were immediately threatened, fire officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Several fire engines, a tanker truck, and hand crews were called in as the 10 
p.m. fire spread quickly over 20 acres of hillside about one-quarter mile from 
the school. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a full brush response," said Charles Carranza, spokesman for the Ventura 
County Fire Department. He said 8 to 10 m.p.h. winds were fanning the blaze. 
</P>
<P>
 He said the fire was headed toward the Piru Mansion, but was no immediate 
threat. 
</P>
<P>
 A nearby resident said sprinklers were turned on at the school. 
</P>
<P>
 "The whole area is burning," said Jon Hur, referring to the blaze that he 
could see from his Center Street home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
