<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEALS FOR THE NEEDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Charities offering meals to the needy today include: 
</P>
<P>
 * The Salvation Army in Ventura will serve traditional Thanksgiving dinners 
from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. at 155 S. Oak St. The meals are available to homeless 
men and women, families and seniors. Call 648-5031 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Vince Corner Family Lodge, a part of Project Understanding, will provide 
meals for the needy at 43 E. Vince St. in Ventura. Call 652-1326 for more 
information. 
</P>
<P>
 * The American Red Cross will offer a traditional Thanksgiving dinner from 8 
to 8:30 p.m. at the California Army National Guard Armory at 351 S. K St. in 
Oxnard. Call 339-2234 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * New Harvest Christian Fellowship, a Food Share agency that also offers 
shelter to homeless men, will serve Thanksgiving dinners at 838 W. 3rd St. in 
Oxnard. Call 985-8176 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * Grace Brethren Church will hold a potluck meal from 5 to 7 p.m. at 2762 
Avenida Simi in Simi Valley. Call 527-0195 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dominion Christian Center will offer Thanksgiving meals from 3 to 6 p.m. at 
1376 Thousand Oaks Blvd. in Thousand Oaks. Call 497-1503 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * Evangelical Free Church is offering free Thanksgiving meals for the 
homeless, the elderly and others in need from 4 to 6 p.m. at 999 Rancho Conejo 
Blvd. in Newbury Park. Call 498-6613 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ecumenical Ministry in Ojai will serve Thanksgiving dinners from 12:30 to 3 
p.m. at the campus of World University of America-Ojai at 107 N. Ventura St. 
Call 646-1444 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Ojai Valley Family Shelter, which is operated by the First Baptist 
Church of Ojai, will offer meals. Call 646-5226 for more information. GREG 
RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
