<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Today is Thanksgiving. The following is the holiday schedule: 
</P>
<P>
 * All city, county and state offices will be closed today and Friday.Federal 
offices will be closed today but open Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 * County and state courthouses will be closed today and Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 * City and county libraries will be closed today and Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Banks and savings and loans will be closed today but open Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Schools: There will be no classes today and Friday; school offices, 
including those at colleges and universities, will be closed.  
</P>
<P>
 * Mail: There will be no mail delivery today, but it will resume Friday. All 
post offices will be closed today, and mail deposited in mailboxes will be 
picked up according to the posted holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trash: There will be no trash pickup by city or county refuse workers today. 
Trash pickups will be a day late for the rest of the week in unincorporated 
areas of the county and in most cities, with the exceptions of Anaheim, Brea, 
Garden Grove, Orange, Placentia and Yorba Linda. In those cities, residents 
with trash pickup today should put their trash out Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 * Buses: Orange County Transportation Authority buses will run on the holiday 
schedule today. There will be no dial-a-ride or car-pool services available. 
</P>
<P>
 * Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be 
closed today and Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
