</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Standing behind the front counter of the Irvine planning department is quite 
an experience for city planner Glen Worthington. 
</P>
<P>
 "Where else besides a front counter can a planner talk to someone who is 
proposing a $1-million development project, and the next minute help a 
homeowner figure out how to turn a back-of-an-envelope sketch into a room 
addition?" Worthington wrote in a recent issue of Planning magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 "And where else does a planner face the challenge of explaining with a 
straight face why the viewing of 'specified anatomical parts' requires a 
conditional-use permit, as I did once when reviewing a request for an adult 
theater?" he continued. 
