<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; ARIZONA ST. WRAPS UP MAUI TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mario Bennett did what was expected inside and the rest of the Arizona State 
Sun Devils took care of things from the outside Wednesday night during a 97-90 
victory over seventh-ranked Maryland in the championship game of the Maui 
Invitational at Lahaina, Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
 Bennett more than held his own against Maryland center Joe Smith and the Sun 
Devils (3-0) used a late three-point barrage -- four from three players in a 
2:23 span -- to take a 79-70 lead with 3:33 to play.They only made one more 
field goal the rest of the way as Maryland (2-1) repeatedly put them on the 
foul line. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona State made 16 of 26 free throws in the final three minutes and the 
Terrapins got no closer than four points. 
</P>
<P>
 Isaac Burton led Arizona State with 23 points. Bennett had 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Exree Hipp scored 25 points and Smith scored 23 for Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 13 Michigan 73, Utah 69 -- Ray Jackson and Jimmy King, the veterans on a 
young Michigan team, combined for 42 points in the third-place game of the Maui 
Invitational. 
</P>
<P>
 Tulane 86, No. 11 Indiana 68 -- LaVeldro Simmons scored 24 points to lead the 
Green Wave (2-1) over the Hoosiers (1-2) in the fifth-place game of the Maui 
Invitational. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 23 Ohio University 82, George Washington 76 -- Geno Ford made two 
three-point shots and then dropped in five free throws down the stretch to lift 
the Bobcats (3-0) in the semifinals of the Preseason NIT at New York. 
</P>
<P>
 Ohio University plays New Mexico State in Friday night's championship game. 
The Aggies staged a furious comeback, scoring 16 of the last 17 points to 
defeat Memphis, 81-78, in the other semifinal. 
</P>
