COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GONZALES LEADS CYPRESS TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Gil Gonzales made seven three-pointers for a game-high 21 points to 
lead Cypress to a 113-72 victory over Los Angeles Trade Tech in nonconference 
men's basketball Wednesday night at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Cummins had 19 points and Matt Kenney added 18, including four 
three-pointers, for the Chargers.Cypress (5-1) connected on 17 of 31 from 
three-point range. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenney led the Chargers with eight assists and Cummins and Jason Krauss each 
had a team-high seven rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ernest Moore scored 22 points and Lawrence Dierbeck added 21 for Los Angeles 
Trade Tech (0-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In another nonconference men's basketball game: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos 94, Rancho Santiago 87 -- Nick Holt scored 21 points, Jon Surface had 
16 and Marlon Watson had 10 points, seven rebounds and six assists for Rancho 
Santiago (3-1). Cerritos (5-0) was led by Darius Rutledge's game-high 25 
points. 
