<P>
PREP WATER POLO; SOUTH PASADENA WINS ANOTHER TITLE, 10-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK STRODER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Craig Bessenger scored three goals, two in the pivotal third quarter, to lead 
South Pasadena High to a 10-7 victory over Whittier La Serna on Wednesday in 
the Southern Section Division III water polo final at Belmont Plaza Pool in 
Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers, who won the Division IV championship last year, built upon a 6-5 
halftime lead by outscoring the Lancers, 4-0, in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 With the victory, No. 2-seeded South Pasadena (23-5) avenged two 
regular-season losses to top-seeded La Serna (22-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Shawn Estep scored four goals for the Tigers, and Brian Butcher scored two. La 
Serna was led by Justin McLaughlin and Jeff Sato, who each scored two goals. 
</P>
<P>
 In other matches, Esperanza won the Division II title with a 9-8 victory over 
Anaheim Servite and Rowland defeated Brea Olinda, 11-8, for the Division VI 
title. MARK STRODER 
</P>
