<P>
 Yoshimura enters his second season with possibly even more strife than his 
first. Like last year, he has to replace all five starters again, but this time 
he doesn't have 11 seniors to choose from as replacements. "We have to replace 
88% of our scoring, 87% of our rebounding and 87% of our assists," Yoshimura 
said. "And we have little varsity experience." Adding to Valencia's woes, two 
of Yoshimura's returning players--Gray and Secoda--are busy with football 
playoffs. Gray (5.2 points) and Secoda (1.1) are being counted on to become the 
team's main scorers. Hoping to ease the burden is Gamboa, a transfer from El 
Dorado. "A real slasher," Yoshimura said of Gamboa. "When the game starts, he's 
real tough and doesn't back down. He will get minutes." To win the league title 
again would border on miraculous, but the playoffs are a realistic goal. Still, 
Yoshimura--like a couple of other Orange League coaches--may need all of the 
nonleague games to figure out what works. SCHEDULE 
