<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: YOUTHS: FUNDS FOR MENTAL HEALTH PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County Mental Health Department has agreed to a contract with 
two Westside family health services to expand programs for adolescents with 
serious mental health problems. 
</P>
<P>
 Vista Del Mar Child and Family Services and Hathaway Children's Services were 
allocated a total of $450,000 to implement a two-year, countywide program to 
increase quality home-based services for young people with mental problems. 
</P>
<P>
 The centers will cooperate in a joint program that includes a comprehensive 
array of mental health services, crisis intervention, case management and 
medication support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
