<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY / COMMUNITY NEWS: MANHATTAN BEACH; CHEVRON GIVES $25,000 TO HELP CITY 
LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chevron Oil Co. has donated $25,000 to Manhattan Beach to benefit the city's 
library. 
</P>
<P>
 The donation, made at a Nov. 15 City Council meeting, will help city officials 
upgrade the technology used in cataloguing books, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'd like to put some things on CD-ROM," said Jim Wolfe, city Parks and 
Recreation director. "That's the way things are going these days." 
</P>
<P>
 The city has spent thousands of dollars this year to keep the library open 
additional hours after the county cut funding for library services. As a 
result, the library's services have been neglected, Wolfe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city's library commission is expected to recommend how the money should be 
spent before a final decision is made, he said. JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
