<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEVELOPMENT: OK OF APARTMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your article on Sunday, Nov. 6, "Panel OKs Apartment Complex Near Tribal 
Springs" was nearly correct, with the exception of two details.There has been a 
change of heart by the Tongva Tribal Council. Martin Alcala, Tongva Tribal 
Council chairman, rescinded the tribe's support given to Barrington Plaza Ltd. 
</P>
<P>
 Also missing from your report was that Councilman Marvin Braude, in whose 
district the Barrington Plaza Project is situated, gave an impassioned plea to 
the committee to disapprove the project on the grounds that it would exacerbate 
an already terrible traffic problem in West Los Angeles, specifically at 
Wilshire and Barrington. 
</P>
<P>
 REGINE WOOD, Los Angeles  
</P>
</TEXT>
