<HEADLINE>
<P>
DINING; CHRISTMAS MENUS MAKE EATING OUT INVITING; RESTAURATEURS OFFER PLENTY OF 
DISHES TO TEMPT YOU AWAY FROM YOUR OWN KITCHEN AND FREE YOU UP TO ENJOY A 
COOKING-FREE HOLIDAY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RODNEY BOSCH, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 So you've had it up to here with culinary servitude. This is the year you 
finally heed Harry Truman's advice and free yourself from holiday cooking 
chores. 
</P>
<P>
 Go ahead, take time to join that pinochle game with the in-laws. Sink into the 
cushy recliner and take your crack at the eggnog and Aunt Bertha's fruitcake. 
</P>
<P>
 If you're thinking of eating out this holiday season, we've done some of the 
legwork to help you decide what to eat and where. 
</P>
<P>
 Figuring your Thanksgiving dining plans have long been solidified, we came up 
with a list of just some of the Ventura County restaurants serving Christmas 
Eve and Christmas Day meals. 
</P>
<P>
 The selection process was about as scientific as channel surfing between 
football games and as arbitrary as choosing which log to toss into the 
fireplace. 
</P>
<P>
 But what follows are several alternatives to plunging your arms into another 
turkey cavity. The list runs the gamut from sumptuous traditional feasts to a 
variety of ethnic cuisines. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Some of the restaurants contacted have not decided on their Christmas 
holiday menus just yet, but were able to provide a pretty good idea of what you 
can expect. 
</P>
<P>
 The Greek at the Harbor, 1583 Spinnaker Drive, Suite 101, Ventura; 650-5350: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (5 to 10 p.m.) and Christmas Day (noon to 8 p.m.). Choose 
from the regular menu or the holiday dinner, which includes a few options: 
choice of stuffed turkey breast, rack of lamb or spiral ham. The holiday dinner 
will include appetizers, salad and dessert choices. Cost: $17.95 for adults, 
$8.95 for children. There will also be traditional Greek dancing and belly 
dancing. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai Valley Inn, Country Club Drive, Ojai; 646-5511: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve and Christmas Day (see hours below). On Christmas Eve in 
the Vista dining room, the inn will offer a la carte "Classic Christmas dinner" 
items such as duckling, roasted turkey, standing rib roast and pecan pie. 
Dinner is from 6 to 9:30 p.m. and there will be piano entertainment. For 
Christmas Eve in the Topa Ballroom, there will be a single 6 p.m. seating for a 
special five-course meal with wine, champagne, storytelling and carolers. The 
package is $50 per adult, $20 for children under 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Christmas Day in the Vista dining room includes the regular buffet service 
until 10:30 a.m. Next up, the Christmas buffet, which will be served from noon 
to 4 p.m., and includes a carving station with ham, turkey and beef, plus 
seafood, pastas and more; $26 adults, $12 children under 12. Christmas dinner 
from 6 to 9 p.m. includes the regular menu service and Christmas specials. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Wheeler Hot Springs restaurant, 16825 Maricopa Highway, above Ojai; 646-8131: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (5 to 9:30 p.m.), Wheeler will offer its regular menu as 
well as a special prix fixe holiday menu. This will include tossed salad of 
mixed baby greens; choice of appetizer, gratin of oysters or duck foie gras; 
Christmas lime sorbet; choice of entree -- roasted partridge porcini or panache 
of the sea (Maine lobster, scallops, sea bass and salmon served with lobster 
and saffron sauces); and dessert, brandy croque-en-bouche. Prix fixe dinner: 
$45 per person. The ever-intriguing jazz pianist Milcho Leviev will perform 
during dinner hours. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Pastabilities, 4910 Verdugo Way, Camarillo; 383-3388: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (4 to 9 p.m.), the Italian eatery plans to have a special 
dinner menu for Christmas Eve diners. However, the restaurant, which 
specializes in, you guessed it, pasta, said it was too early to tell what that 
menu might include. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Gallery Restaurant at the Doubletree Hotel, 2055 E. Harbor Blvd., Ventura; 
643-6000: 
</P>
<P>
 Christmas Day champagne brunch (12 to 6 p.m.) will be served buffet-style with 
salads, appetizers, seafood, fruits, plus roasted turkey, roast beef, 
vegetables and desserts; $20.95, $17.95 senior citizens, $8.95 ages 5 to 12, 
under 5 free. And don't miss the huge gingerbread house in the hotel lobby. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mario's Bistro, 2121 Rose Ave., Oxnard; 983-1323: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (11 to 9 p.m.) and Christmas Day (11 a.m. to about 8 p.m.). 
Chef Neal Rosenthal hasn't sent his holiday menu to the printer -- so to speak 
-- but you can expect some "traditional and non-traditional Christmas fare," he 
said. Besides the regular menu options, Rosenthal is planning a few specials. 
The likely candidates include game bird, pork chops and cod cakes with crepes 
(a Southern Italian dish). "We're going to have some fun with it," Rosenthal 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Victoria Restaurant & Pub, 1413-F S. Victoria Ave., Ventura; 650-0060: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (5 to 9:30 p.m.) and Christmas Day (noon to 6 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
 A Christmas Day banquet for parties of six to 60 will be held from noon to 
about 5 p.m. The first course will include choices of soups and salads. There 
are four entree choices: roast leg of Shropshire pork with traditional 
stuffing, roast potatoes, fresh vegetables and apple sauce; Norfolk roast 
turkey with traditional stuffing, roast potatoes and fresh vegetables; 
vegetable lasagna; fresh charbroiled fish of day served with rice and fresh 
vegetables. Dessert choices: carrot cake, chocolate fudge cake, English sherry 
trifle or fruit crumble. Champagne, coffee and English party favors are 
included with the meal. Cost: adults $19.95, children 12 and under $9.95. 
</P>
<P>
 A similar offering for the Christmas menu will be served both days for $14.95 
per person. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ristorante Fabrizio, 3731 E. Thousand Oaks Blvd., Westlake Village; 496-9033: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (5 to 10 p.m.). Fabrizio Marangoni has penned a rough draft 
menu for his annual Christmas Eve dinner specials, though nothing is written in 
concrete. "Christmas Eve is my second most important night of the year," 
Marangoni said. "It must be special, so we choose the items people like the 
best." You'll have a choice of several entrees, plus salads, appetizers and 
soups. Everything will be served a la carte. Included: filet mignon Monte Carlo 
(charbroiled and topped with shiitake , champagne and other mushrooms) and 
served with prawns; rack of lamb with fresh herbs; pork tenderloin prepared 
with a peppercorn and Chianti sauce; a veal preparation -- Marangoni said he 
hasn't decided on the recipe. Seafood options will include Norwegian salmon in 
a champagne sauce, ahi tuna in a Cabernet mushroom sauce; and a 
bouillabaisse-style seafood combo called "Mamma Mia." Special entrees will be 
priced, Marangoni said, in the neighborhood of $18.95 to $22.95. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Guadalajara, 2891 E. Thousand Oaks Blvd., Thousand Oaks; 497-0070: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve and Christmas Day (11 a.m. to 11 p.m.) Specializing in 
seafood, this Mexican restaurant will serve from its regular menu and spice 
things up a bit with a few holiday specials -- including seafood platters. 
Price range: $5 to $13. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ciao Restaurant, 1627 Los Angeles Ave., Simi Valley; 522-1049: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (5 to 10 p.m.), Ciao's Italian and French cuisine chef will 
prepare a few special entrees that do not appear on the regular menu. Those 
will include: rack of lamb, filet of venison (sauteed and finished with porcini 
mushrooms and topped with goose liver pate); roasted quail (stuffed with veal 
and finished with fresh peppercorn and cognac creme sauce). Specials, served a 
la carte, will range from $25 to $30. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Village Inn Restaurant, 32001 Agoura Road, Westlake Village; 
495-6451: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve (4 to 10 p.m) and Christmas Day (10 a.m. to 8 p.m.). On the 
24th you can order a la carte from the regular menu or choose from several 
Christmas Eve specials. Christmas Day will feature an "extravagant" buffet, 
including roast turkey, honey-baked ham, roast beef, Cornish game hen, Oriental 
stir fry, poached salmon, full breakfast station and more. Cost: $21.95 adults, 
$19.95 senior citizens, $10.95 children. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Hyatt, 880 S. Westlake Blvd, Westlake Village; 497-9991: 
</P>
<P>
 Open Christmas Eve and Christmas Day (noon to 8 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
 Regular menu service will be available for the 24th. Christmas Day dinner will 
feature a buffet-style spread with roasted free range turkey, prime rib, 
honey-mustard glazed ham, sauteed snapper, salads, seafood appetizers and more. 
Estimated cost: $25 adults, $10 children. 
</P>
