<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSINESS; PARTICIPANTS SOUGHT FOR BEIJING EXPOSITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A City of Industry firm organizing a business exposition next year in Beijing 
is inviting American firms to participate. 
</P>
<P>
 Guide Business Group, which acts as a liaison between U.S. and Chinese 
businesses, is planning the six-day exhibition for April. U.S. companies 
interested in expanding into China can display their products and technologies 
at the National Palace in Beijing at the event, which will be co-sponsored by 
the Space, Science and Technology Commission of China. 
</P>
<P>
 The show will feature a variety of enterprises and will be followed by a 
year-round showcase for participants who choose to extend their exhibits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
