<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; TERM-LIMIT PETITION SENT TO CITY CLERK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena resident Nicholas T. Conway has turned in a petition containing about 
14,000 signatures to qualify a ballot measure that seeks to limit City Council 
members to two four-year terms. 
</P>
<P>
 Conway, who ran unsuccessfully for City Council in 1991, turned in the 
petition Tuesday afternoon, City Clerk Maria Stewart said. To qualify for the 
ballot, 9,908 of the signatures must be valid, Stewart said. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart said it is unlikely that county elections officials will be able to 
verify the signatures in time to get the measure on the city's March 7 primary 
election ballot. Instead, if the measure qualifies, it will probably be put 
before voters in the city's April 18 general election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
