<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; MAYOR ANNOUNCES SHE WON'T SEEK REELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena Mayor Kathryn Nack, saying she wants to spend more time with her 
family, has announced she will not run for reelection when her second term on 
the City Council expires in May. 
</P>
<P>
 During a news conference last Friday at City Hall, Nack said her retirement 
has nothing to do with intense infighting sparked by Councilman Isaac Richard, 
who was censured earlier this month after disrupting a council meeting and 
failing to heed Nack's admonishments. 
</P>
<P>
 Nack, 70, said the recent birth of a grandson contributed to her decision. She 
has served on the City Council since 1987 and has been a planning commissioner 
and a member of the Pasadena Unified School District's board of education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
