FUGITIVE AUTHOR VISITS FRANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With hundreds of police protecting her like a head of state, Bangladeshi 
author Taslima Nasrin arrived in France on Wednesday in a challenge to Islamic 
fundamentalists who have called for her death. 
</P>
<P>
 Security was unusually tight at Charles de Gaulle Airport as Nasrin arrived 
for her 10-day visit. 
</P>
