<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; FOOTHILL PRINCIPAL NAMED TO NEW POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foothill High School Principal Janis Jones has been appointed assistant 
superintendent for instructional services of the Tustin Unified School 
District. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Brooks, principal at A.G. Currie Middle School, will take over Jones' 
position at Foothill High School.Both changes will take effect Jan. 30 and a 
temporary principal will be named at A.G. Currie Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 The school district announced the appointments recently, following changes in 
several management positions. Jones replaced Julie Hume, who will return to her 
job as director of curriculum planning. 
</P>
<P>
 Hume was named temporary assistant superintendent for instructional services 
after Peggy Lynch, who held the position, was appointed superintendent of the 
Brea-Olinda Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones served as Foothill High School principal for three years, and was widely 
credited with the school's designation as a California Distinguished School 
this year. She has previously worked in the Perris Union High School District 
and the Huntington Beach Union High School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Brooks has been with the Tustin school district for 10 years, including the 
past three years as principal of A.G. Currie Middle School, which also was 
named a 1994 California Distinguished School. 
</P>
<P>
 A former assistant principal at Hewes Middle School and principal at W.R. 
Nelson Elementary School, Brooks is the president-elect of the Tustin School 
Management Assn. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
