<P>
SCHOOL FOUNDATION WINS FINE ARTS GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster School District's Foundation for Educational Excellence has 
won a $25,000 grant to fund fine arts programs, a district spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Beverly Hills-based Wilbur May Foundation awarded the grant, which will 
provide $5,000 annually for the next five years to fund assemblies and 
workshops covering topics including dance, music and visual arts, district 
spokeswoman Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 This winter, the grant will pay for eight artists to visit schools, including 
a Native American storyteller and musician, a trio that performs dances of 
Hawaii, Samoa and New Zealand, and a performer who uses traditional African 
instruments, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 Founded in 1990, the district foundation has raised more than $80,000 for its 
schools to buy classroom materials and pay for annual student recognition 
awards, academic competitions and student activities, Brown said. 
