<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: CHANG, MCENROE TO PLAY AT THE POND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Chang will play John McEnroe in a charity tennis match to benefit 
Arthur Ashe's Safe Passage Foundation Dec. 28 at The Pond of Anaheim, it was 
announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 McEnroe is the foundation's chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are available at the arena box office and Ticketmaster. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Three Mission Viejo girls' volleyball players have made oral commitments to 
play in college, said Coach Candace Werve of the Mission Valley Volleyball 
Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter Megan Mahoney will play at North Carolina. Middle blocker Jill 
Sievers will play at Colorado State. Middle blocker Meredith Axtell will play 
at William and Mary. 
</P>
