glad we got the stay." Rhodes said an appeal will be filed in the case in the 
next few months.  
</P>
<P>
 Harold Collins, attorney for David Holder, said the actions of the defense 
came as no surprise. "They had indicated that they would file post-trial 
motions and an appeal," he said. 
