<P>
 Czech Luxury Hospital Sale Falls Through: The $46.4-million sale of the Czech 
Republic's most luxurious hospital to a group partly controlled by South 
Africa's Clinic Holdings Ltd. has collapsed, the Czech news agency CTK said. 
The 230-bed hospital, known as Na Homolce, once served former Czechoslovakia's 
top Communist Party officials and is now receiving up to $3.5 million a year 
from the Czech government to stay in operation.Euro Hospital Group Praha is 
made up of Clinic Holdings, a surgical and medical private hospital group in 
Johannesburg, South Africa; Cape Town, South Africa-based Syfin Holdings, and a 
Czech company formed by Na Homolce's director and three head doctors. The group 
won its bid for the sale in January and signed a contract in August. 
