</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MEXICAN STOCKS 
</P>
<P>
 * Mexican stocks plunged after the deputy attorney general resigned and 
accused senior ruling party officials of covering up the investigation into the 
murder of Jose Francisco Ruiz Masseiu, the party's secretary general. The Bolsa 
stock market index fell as much as 75 points to 2,376.23 after the official 
said the top two party leaders had hindered his investigation. * The prospect 
that party officials obstructed the inquiry has again put fractious politics in 
the spotlight, undermining investor confidence. 
</P>
<P>
 * Share prices later recouped some of the losses and closed at 2,416.67. 
Source: Bloomberg Business News SPOTLIGHT: MOROCCO 
</P>
<P>
 Economic reforms encouraged by international lenders have reduced budget 
deficits and led to increased foreign investment. But the economy still suffers 
from a high rate of population growth, high unemployment, the vulnerability of 
agriculture to droughts and an over-reliance on exports of phosphates. 
</P>
