<TEXT>
<P>
 Eldorado Wins Award: Eldorado Bancorp said Wednesday that it had earned the 
Veribanc Blue Ribbon Bank award for the 1994 second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The award is given to financial institutions that demonstrate attention to 
safety, soundness and financial strength. A bank's balance sheet, income 
statement, loan portfolio and compliance with federal capital requirements are 
examined. 
</P>
<P>
 With assets of $311 million, Eldorado Bancorp in Tustin, through principal 
subsidiary Eldorado Bank, operates three commercial loan centers and 10 retail 
branches in Orange County and the Inland Empire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
