<HEADLINE>
<P>
GO POG WILD AT UNIVERSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pogs are the biggest thing since Transformers. POG is an acronym for 
Passion-Orange-Guava, a popular drink in Hawaii. The mostly cardboard bottle 
caps are cheap, easy to collect and store -- and a lot easier to get than most 
toys or games that have exploded into must-have status. 
</P>
<P>
 So what could be a bigger attraction than what's being touted as the "world's 
largest Pog game"? Friday through Sunday, children 3-11 can go Pog wild with 
the game at Universal Studios, Universal City, where PogWorld, an interactive 
play land, has been operating for the past four weekends.  
</P>
<P>
 PogWorld hours are 10:30 a.m.-4:30 p.m. The cost is included in regular theme 
park admission: ages 12-60, $31; ages 3-11 and 60 and older, $24.95. For 
information, call (818) 508-9600. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
