<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: SIGNAL HILL; CITY COUNCIL OKS $12-MILLION BOND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A $12-million bond issue to help the Redevelopment Agency create more sales 
tax revenue for the city and provide additional affordable housing has been 
approved by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 The agency plans to use $4.5 million of the bond proceeds to attract more 
businesses to the Town Center project, $4 million to expand the auto mall and 
$3.5 million to provide affordable housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
