<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: ORANGE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MAGNOLIA 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 19-8 8-2 COACH: Al Walin 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 190-257 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Gary 
Charles Sr. 5-10 G Josh Reding Sr. 6-1 F 04,19,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. 
P Hani Atalli Sr. 6-4 C Don Fisher Sr. 6-3 C Amad Shurdim Jr. 6-3 C Vatha 
Singbandith Jr. 5-9 G Lan Tran Sr. 6-0 F 04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. 
P Donald Benjamin So. 6-1 F Mister McKinney Jr. 6-2 F Henry Welch So. 6-2 F 
OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The two-time league champions, (who tied Valencia for the title last year) 
were depleted by graduation. But a 19-8 summer league record has Walin thinking 
he might not have to rebuild after all. "I didn't know what to think before we 
started," Walin said, "but we played extremely well defensively. It showed we 
had 10 kids we could play." A couple of those are McKinney, a transfer from 
Savanna whom Walin described as "a good athlete," and Todd Jones, who missed 
the summer with a broken wrist but is ready. Like other teams in the Orange 
League, the Sentinels are not overly tall so they will depend on quickness. 
Magnolia will find out early how good it is, playing in three tournaments 
during December. But Walin is optimistic about the prospects. "Our athletic 
ability has gone from way down to the top. We may struggle shooting now and 
then, and may not beat the top teams, but I think we can beat everybody else. I 
still think we have a shot to win three times." SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 December 1-3 at Orange Lutheran tournament; 5-10 at the Costa Mesa Kiwanis 
tournament; 14 at Loara; 15 vs. Garden Grove; 16 at Katella; 21 vs. Sonora; 
26-30 at Canyon tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 January 6 vs. Savanna; 11 at Western; 13 at Brea-Olinda; 18 at Valencia; 20 
vs. Anaheim; 27 at Savanna. 
</P>
<P>
 February 1 vs. Western; 3 vs. Brea-Olinda; 8 vs. Valencia; 10 at Anaheim. 
</P>
